<apex:page tabStyle="LogConfiguration__c" showHeader="false" standardStylesheets="true">
    
    <style>
        body {background: url('{!URLFOR("/img/in-page_clouds.png")}') top left no-repeat;}
    </style>

        <apex:pageBlock mode="maindetail">
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="About Log Configuration:" columns="2" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p>By making use of a meaningful grouping key, the LogWriter process and LogInitializer process work together to surface the status of a message at various points in one or more Sequence(s) </p>
                    <p>The Log Initializer process defines the grouping key.</p>
                    <p>The Log LogWriter process surface the status of a message using the grouping key defined under a prior Log Initializer process.</p>
                    <p>The  grouping key is a composite of "a Time Stamp" and "A Business Identifier"</p>
                    <p>The business identifier (the non-time stamp portion of the  grouping key) can be configured in be one of the three ways:
                        <ul>
                            <li>Implicit Key</li>
                            <li>Explicit Static Key</li>    
                            <li>Explicit Dynamic Key</li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                    <p><img width="480" src="{!URLFOR($Resource.HelpZip, '/LogConfiguration/Log.png')}" /></p>
                    
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>

            </apex:pageBlockSection>

 
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="Implicit Key Configuration :" columns="1" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p>When no explicit definition of the business identifier has been configured on the LogInitializer process, the business identifier will be a a composite of the LogInitializer's Sequence name and Sequence Position.
                       Whenever a message passes through a LogInitializer process with an Implicit Key Configuration , a log grouping record will be created immediately using this default composite Group Identifier.
                    </p>   
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>
      
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="Explicit Static Key Configuration:" columns="1" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                
                    <p>Under this configuration, the business identifier is statically defined in the form of a meaningful constant (eg INVOICE, WEB-DATA-FROM-YAHOO) 
                       Whenever a message passes through a LogInitializer process with an Explicit Static Key Configuration, a log grouping record will be created immediately using this this value defined by the Static Group Identifier.
                    </p>   
                    <p>To define a dynamic Static Group Identifier, enter a value in the editable Static Group Identifier text field.</p>
                    <p><b> Note : </b> If the Static Group Identifier field is valued, the Dynamic Group Identifier should not be valued.</p> 
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection>
             
             
            <apex:pageBlockSection title="Explicit Dynamic Key Configuration:" columns="1" collapsible="false">
                <apex:pageBlockSectionItem >
                    <p>Under this configuration, the business identifier is dynamically extracted from the SObject using the field name  defined in the Dynamic Group Identifier.
                       Whenever a message passes through a LogInitializer process with an Explicit Dynamic Key Configuration, a log grouping record will be created immediately using a data property of that specific message as defined by the Dynamic Group Identifier.
                    </p>   
                    <p>To define a dynamic Group Identifier, click the [Change Dynamic Group Identifier] button to reveal a Sobject field selection page.</p>
                    <p>From the Choose Object Name, select the required field's parent SOBject from the dropdown list (eg Account, CreditCheck__c, etc). 
                       The associated field drop down list will be enabled after the selection of a valid SObject.
                    </p>
                    <p><b> Note : </b> If the Dynamic Group Identifier is valued, the Static Group Identifier should not be valued.</p>
                </apex:pageBlockSectionItem>
            </apex:pageBlockSection> 
            
        </apex:pageBlock>

</apex:page>